// LA-30 B2 (doc 06 §2) — CancelledException is an ordinary IException carrier:
// catchable by its own type, by its interface (ICancelledException), and by the
// root IException, and it carries a message like any Exception. This is the
// language-floor half of B2 (the CancelledException class); delivery of the
// exception at a task's park point is the separate substrate work (§5). A pure
// prelude class with no task machinery, so byte-identical on oracle/IR/LLVM.
try {
    throw CancelledException("stop");
} catch (CancelledException e) {
    console.writeln("by-type: " + e.message);
}

try {
    throw CancelledException("halt");
} catch (ICancelledException e) {
    console.writeln("by-iface: " + e.message);
}

try {
    throw CancelledException("done");
} catch (IException e) {
    console.writeln("by-root: " + e.message);
}
